law.text:
To convert to a commercial bank, a capital stock savings and loan shall deliver to the Commissioner:
A filing fee of $1,000;
An application for conversion;
A certified copy of the resolution of the board of directors that authorizes the conversion;
The proposed amended charter and bylaws amendments;
The proposed notice of the meeting to consider conversion, and the time and manner in which notice will be given to stockholders;
The proposed proxy statement;
The proposed plan of conversion; and
Any additional documents required by the Commissioner.
